{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17650462","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17650462"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:11:52+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:11:52+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18402"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18402","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18402"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11120"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74485"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11120","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11120"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18402"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59976"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7116"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25778"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25782"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74485","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74485"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following brain regions processes sensory information leading to purposeful movement and innervates the pre-motor and supplementary motor regions?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Motor cortex","Primary somatic sensory cortex","Posterior parietal cortex","Prefrontal cortex","Cerebellum"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe brain is responsible for processing sensory information and coordinating motor functions. Different regions of the brain have specific roles in these processes. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior parietal cortex\u003C/strong\u003E is involved in processing sensory information and integrating it to plan and coordinate purposeful movements. It sends information to the pre-motor and supplementary motor regions to help initiate and guide movements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMotor cortex\u003C/strong\u003E - This region is primarily involved in the execution of voluntary movements rather than processing sensory information\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrimary somatic sensory cortex\u003C/strong\u003E - This area processes tactile information from the body but does not directly coordinate movement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrefrontal cortex\u003C/strong\u003E - This region is involved in higher cognitive functions such as decision-making and does not directly process sensory information for movement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECerebellum\u003C/strong\u003E - This structure is involved in the coordination and fine-tuning of movements but does not process sensory information for initiating movement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The posterior parietal cortex processes sensory information and integrates it to plan and coordinate purposeful movements.","The primary somatic sensory cortex is responsible for processing tactile information from the body.","The motor cortex is involved in the execution of voluntary movements."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook 